==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quean
<hw>Quean</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Originally, a woman,
AS. <ets>cwene</ets>; akin to OS. <ets>quena</ets>, OHG.
<ets>quena</ets>, Icel. <ets>kona</ets>, Goth <ets>qin<?/</ets>, and AS.
<ets>cw⟦eacute⟧n</ets>, also to Gr. <?/ woman, wife, Skr.
<ets>gn⟦amac⟧</ets> goddess. Cf. <er>Queen</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A woman; a young or unmarried woman; a girl.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A low woman; a wench; a slut.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The dread
of every scolding <xex>quean</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Gay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Queasily</ent>⟦br⟧
